            <ArticleTitle>Multiplexed single-molecule assay for enzymatic activity on flow-stretched DNA.</ArticleTitle>
            <Pagination>
                <MedlinePgn>397-9</MedlinePgn>
            </Pagination>
            <Abstract>
                <AbstractText>We report a single-molecule assay for nucleic-acid enzymes on flow-stretched DNA templates. To facilitate the detection of slow or intermittent enzymatic activities, we developed the assay with 15-nm spatial resolution at a frame rate of 1 Hz and approximately 10 nm mechanical stability over the timescale of hours. With multiplexed data collection, we applied the assay to phi29 DNA polymerase, HIV-1 reverse transcriptase, lambda exonuclease and Escherichia coli RNA polymerase.</AbstractText>
            </Abstract>
